cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR

This paper addresses the problem of human re-identification in crowded scenes using computer vision techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also incorporates modeling of personal, social, and environmental constraints, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach using Cumulative Matching Curves and 1-1 assignment, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
